  "prompt": "Does blind person from birth dream?",
  "response": "Yes, individuals who are blind from birth do experience dreams, but their dreams differ from those of sighted individuals. People who are blind from birth typically do not have visual imagery in their dreams; instead, their dreams are often rich in sounds, touch, tastes, smells, and emotions. Their experiences in dreams are shaped by their other senses and the experiences they have in waking life. This highlights the brain's ability to create complex experiences and narratives based on non-visual information.",
